	heroObjectPosition={`center center`}
	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">If you’re a husband, the Father’s Heart Bible™ is for you.</strong> You’re called to love your wife as Christ loved the church — to provide, to cover, to lay your life down — often while quietly wondering if you measure up at all. The <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father’s Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free on any phone — and it reveals the God you’re trying to imitate as <em>Father</em>, from Genesis to Revelation. Whether you’re searching for “Bible verses for husbands,” “how to love my wife biblically,” or just strength to keep showing up, it begins in one place: before you are a husband, you are a beloved son.`}
	keyTakeaway={`You cannot give a love you have not received. Before you are a husband, you are a son of God — so let your Father love you first, and then love your wife from the overflow, not from an empty tank.`}
	painsHeading={`The weight husbands carry`}
	painsIntroHtml={`Behind the steady provider and the man who “has it handled,” many husbands are quietly running on empty — carrying the pressure to provide, the fear of falling short, and a loneliness they’ve never said out loud. The strain is real, and it’s often invisible until it shows up in the marriage itself.`}
