	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Notice the thread running through it: a man can be deeply committed to his marriage and still be starving on the inside. He’s told to be the rock, so he hides the cracks. He’s told to provide, so he measures his worth by a paycheck. He’s told to lead, so he leads from exhaustion instead of love — and slowly the very strength he’s straining to give runs dry.</p><p>None of this means you’re a bad husband or a failing man. It means you’re a son who has been pouring out without being filled. There is a Father who sees the weight you carry in silence, and who is after <em>you</em> — the man — long before He is after your performance as a husband.</p>`}
