	aFatherHeading={`A Father for husbands`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>The answer to a worn-out husband is not a better budget, a productivity system, or gritting your teeth to try harder. It is not even a marriage book read as one more duty. The answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a holy Father for a beloved son who happens to be married.</p><p>Scripture sets a staggering standard: love your wife <em>as Christ loved the church</em>, laying your life down for her. But here is the mercy hidden in that command — Christ’s love is not first something you produce; it is something you <em>receive</em>. You cannot give a covering you have never stood under. You cannot pour out a love you have never been filled with. Before you can love like the Son, you must be loved like a son.</p><p>So you wake up tomorrow not first to perform as a husband, not first to provide — but to be <em>loved</em> by your Father. Marriage is what overflows after. Your Father isn’t grading how well you lead; He is delighting in His boy. And a man who knows he is fathered finally has something real to give the woman he loves.</p>`}
