	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; Martin Luther, George MacDonald, and Andrew Murray (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>When our Father said, “Let there be light,” there was light. His Word does what He sends it to do. The same love He speaks over you will not come back empty — not in your heart, and not in the home you’re learning to cover.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">“My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose.” <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What the Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>“Son, before you ever provided a dollar or led your home a single day, I delighted in you. You are not measured by your paycheck or your performance; you are My beloved boy, and you always have been.</p><p>Put down the weight of being everything to everyone for a moment. You were never meant to be the source — only a son who comes to Me and is filled. Let Me love you in the places no one sees, where you’re tired and afraid you’re not enough. I am not disappointed in you. Receive My love, and then go home and love her with what I’ve poured into you. You cannot give what you have not received — so come, receive, and overflow. I am your Father, and you are Mine.”</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for husbands`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You and praise You for all husbands — the ones who carry the quiet weight of providing, covering, and laying their lives down, often while wondering if they measure up. Let them hear Your whisper above the pressure to perform and the fear of falling short. Let them encounter Your love — not as a standard they strain to meet, but as a weight they feel — and experience Your delight over them, apart from any paycheck, any success, any measure of how well they lead.</p><p>Give them grace to prioritize intimacy with You above their striving, and to receive their identity as Your sons before they are husbands. Father, fill these men so full of Your love that they have something real to give their wives — teach them that they cannot give a love they have not first received, and let them love from the overflow. Strengthen their marriages, soften every harshness, and heal the orphan place that drives a man to prove himself.</p><p>I pray Your protection over them from the enemy, from temptation, from lust and isolation, and from despair. Let them know there is no condemnation in You. Let them know You, their Father, as their true inheritance and reward, for every other gift pales beside the gift of You. And may they wake up every single day under the pour of their heavenly Father’s heart for them.</p><p>In Jesus’ name, amen.</p>`}
