		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for husbands?`, answer: `Ephesians 5:25 (love your wife as Christ loved the church), 1 Peter 3:7 (live with her in an understanding way, showing honor), Colossians 3:19 (love your wife and do not be harsh), 1 Corinthians 13 (love is patient and kind), and 1 John 4:19 (we love because He first loved us) all speak directly to husbands. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about how a husband should love his wife?`, answer: `Ephesians 5:25 sets the standard: love your wife as Christ loved the church and gave Himself up for her — a sacrificial, self-giving love. But that love is first received, not manufactured: 1 John 4:19 says we love because He first loved us. A husband loves his wife well out of the overflow of being loved by his Father, not from willpower alone. You can read these passages free with audio in the Father's Heart Bible™.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say to a husband who feels like he's failing?`, answer: `You are not measured by your performance. Galatians 4:7 says you are no longer a slave but a son and heir — your worth is your sonship, not your paycheck or how well you lead. 1 John 4:19 reminds you that you love because you were first loved. If you feel like you're falling short, the Father's Heart Bible™ lets you read these passages free, with audio, and meet a Father who delights in you as a son before He ever weighs you as a husband.` },
